<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFScott_McLemee1996">Scott McLemee (Dec. 1996). "The Quigley Cult". <i><a href="/wiki/George_(magazine)" title="George (magazine)">George Magazine</a></i> <b>1</b> (10): 96, 98.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Quigley+Cult&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BGeorge+%28magazine%29%7CGeorge+Magazine%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Scott+McLemee&amp;rft.au=Scott+McLemee&amp;rft.date=Dec.+1996&amp;rft.volume=1&amp;rft.issue=10&amp;rft.pages=96%2C+98&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Carroll_Quigley"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BCleon_Skousen.7CW._Cleon_Skousen.5D.5D1970"><a href="/wiki/Cleon_Skousen" title="Cleon Skousen">W. Cleon Skousen</a> (1970). <i>The Naked Capitalist: A Review and Commentary on Dr. Carroll Quigley’s Book “Tragedy and Hope”</i>. Salt Lake City, UT: privately published. pp.&#160;1-6, 38-44 (communists), 6-24 (bankers), 26-38 (Rhodes and Milner), 45-48 (IPR), 50-57 (CFR).</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Naked+Capitalist%3A+A+Review+and+Commentary+on+Dr.+Carroll+Quigley%E2%80%99s+Book+%E2%80%9CTragedy+and+Hope%E2%80%9D&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BCleon+Skousen%7CW.+Cleon+Skousen%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BCleon+Skousen%7CW.+Cleon+Skousen%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1970&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B1-6%2C+38-44+%28communists%29%2C+6-24+%28bankers%29%2C+26-38+%28Rhodes+and+Milner%29%2C+45-48+%28IPR%29%2C+50-57+%28CFR%29&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+UT&amp;rft.pub=privately+published&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Carroll_Quigley"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BGary_Allen.5D.5D_with_Larry_Abraham1971"><a href="/wiki/Gary_Allen" title="Gary Allen">Gary Allen</a> with Larry Abraham (1971). <i>None Dare Call It Conspiracy</i>. Rossmoor, CA: Concord Press.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=None+Dare+Call+It+Conspiracy&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BGary+Allen%5D%5D+with+Larry+Abraham&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BGary+Allen%5D%5D+with+Larry+Abraham&amp;rft.date=1971&amp;rft.place=Rossmoor%2C+CA&amp;rft.pub=Concord+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Carroll_Quigley"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Quigley is cited on pp. 12-13, 39, 42, 57, 59, 79-82, 85; his photo is on p. 52.</li>
<li id="cite_note-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19" title="">^</a></b> For example, a quotation from Quigley is displayed on the back cover of <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFJohn_F._McManus2004">John F. McManus (2004). <i>The Insiders: Architects of the New World Order</i>. Appleton, WI: <a href="/wiki/John_Birch_Society" title="John Birch Society">John Birch Society</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Insiders%3A+Architects+of+the+New+World+Order&amp;rft.aulast=John+F.+McManus&amp;rft.au=John+F.+McManus&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.place=Appleton%2C+WI&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BJohn+Birch+Society%5D%5D&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Carroll_Quigley"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
